abstract:

Speaker:: Cheuk Ting Ho Track: PyCon: Python Language Recently, a paper is published to demonstrate how a visibly valid contribution can contain malicious code by exporting the Unicode control characters. Some of these attacks has been tested on Python and it works. Shall the Python and open-source communities be concerned? Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022. https://2022.pycon.de More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/HYGPW9 Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
